Task 1: Set up Covenant for Command and Control Operations
Subtask 1.1: Install Prerequisites and Dependencies
First, we need to ensure all required packages are installed on the system.

# Update system packages
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install required dependencies
sudo apt install -y git curl wget unzip build-essential

# Install .NET SDK (required for Covenant)
wget https://packages.microsoft.com/config/ubuntu/22.04/packages-microsoft-prod.deb -O packages-microsoft-prod.deb
sudo dpkg -i packages-microsoft-prod.deb
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y dotnet-sdk-6.0

# Verify .NET installation
dotnet --version
Subtask 1.2: Clone and Build Covenant
Download and compile the Covenant C2 framework from the official repository.

# Create working directory
mkdir -p ~/redteam-lab
cd ~/redteam-lab

# Clone Covenant repository
git clone --recurse-submodules https://github.com/cobbr/Covenant.git
cd Covenant/Covenant

# Build Covenant
dotnet build
Subtask 1.3: Configure Covenant Database
Set up the database configuration for Covenant operations.

# Navigate to Covenant directory
cd ~/redteam-lab/Covenant/Covenant

# Create appsettings.json configuration
cat > appsettings.json << 'EOF'
{
  "ConnectionStrings": {
    "DefaultConnection": "Data Source=Data/covenant.db"
  },
  "CovenantUrl": "https://0.0.0.0:7443",
  "CovenantBindUrl": "0.0.0.0",
  "CovenantPort": 7443,
  "Logging": {
    "LogLevel": {
      "Default": "Information",
      "Microsoft": "Warning",
      "Microsoft.Hosting.Lifetime": "Information"
    }
  }
}
EOF

# Initialize database
dotnet ef database update
Subtask 1.4: Start Covenant Server
Launch the Covenant C2 server and perform initial setup.

# Start Covenant server
cd ~/redteam-lab/Covenant/Covenant
dotnet run &

# Wait for server to start
sleep 30

# Check if Covenant is running
netstat -tlnp | grep 7443
Subtask 1.5: Access Covenant Web Interface
Open a new terminal and set up access to the Covenant web interface.

